Detailed Description

cvmx_sriomaint::_ir_buffer_config2

This register controls the RX and TX buffer availability by priority. The typical values are optimized for normal operation. Care must be taken when changing these values to avoid values which can result in deadlocks. Disabling a priority is not recommended and can result in system level failures.
